3) RIGHT JOIN: fetch all records from right table and try to match with left table


  e.g.
    =->select*from tbl_order;               =->select id,user_name from user;

        +----+---------+----------+         +----+-----------+
        | id | cust_id | order_id |         | id | user_name |
        +----+---------+----------+         +----+-----------+   
        |  1 |       1 |        4 |         |  1 | mustved   |
        |  1 |       1 |        4 |         |  2 | aaaa      |
        |  2 |       3 |        2 |         |  3 | bbb       |
        |  3 |       4 |        1 |         |  4 | cccc      |
        |  4 |       1 |        5 |         |  5 | dddd      |
        |  5 |       7 |        2 |         +----+-----------+
        |  6 |       4 |        8 |
        +----+---------+----------+
     
 ->select user.user_name as name,tbl_order.cust_id
        from user
        right join tbl_order
        on user.id=tbl_order.cust_id;
            +---------+---------+
            | name    | cust_id |
